  "prompt": "Why am I getting Likes from people in India when my ad campaign is targeted only to people in SF?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you are receiving Likes from people in India on your ad campaign that is targeted at San Francisco:\n\n1. **Targeting Settings**: Double-check your ad targeting settings to ensure there are no errors or misconfigurations. Make sure the geographic location is correctly set to San Francisco and that no other locations are included.\n\n2. **VPNs and Proxies**: Some users might be using VPNs or proxies that make it appear as though they are located in San Francisco when they are actually in India.\n\n3. **Ad Sharing**: Your ad might be shared by users in San Francisco, and their friends or followers in India could be seeing and interacting with it.\n\n4. **Platform Glitches**: Sometimes, social media platforms experience glitches or errors that can result in ads being shown outside the targeted area.\n\n5. **Interest Targeting**: If your ad targeting includes specific interests or behaviors that are common globally, users outside of your targeted geographic location may still see and interact with your ad.\n\n6. **Lookalike Audiences**: If you are using lookalike audiences, the platform might be expanding the reach beyond the specified geographic location to include users with similar profiles.\n\n7. **Organic Reach**: After initial interaction from your targeted audience, the ad might gain organic reach, including users from other locations.\n\nTo address this issue, review your campaign settings, monitor the analytics closely, and consider reaching out to the support team of the advertising platform for assistance in resolving any discrepancies.",
